top_review: I've tried the yellow/green/orange tapes. I now use yellow exclusively. Plenty of experience with it while painting my entire house from bare plaster, with walls different colours to ceiling, so always having to tape the ceiling as well as doorframes/skirting/etc.It's not very high tack; that's the green one, which I found way too tacky for wall paint. The orange one conversely is nowhere near tacky enough - it doesn't stay attached to surfaces with regular matt paint. The yellow one sticks well and peels off easily enough. The only issue is, will it pull off any paint with it?There are load of reviews of it pulling off large chunks of paint. Based solely on my own experience of it mostly being good but occasionally pulling some paint off, I would say this: if the paint on your wall wasn't done properly, this tape may pull it off. By which I mean, if someone painted a top coat directly on unpainted plaster, or the surface under the current top coat was dirty, or anything which would cause the paint to not be attached to the surface below as well as it should, then this tape may pull it off.When I've pulled it off the few areas I knew weren't painted correctly (e.g. top coat directly over plaster or filler with no mist coat), it often pulled the paint off. However the vast, vast majority of it was done properly - couple mist coats, couple top coats - and although I still got the occasional tiny spec pulled off, for the most part it comes off easily and cleanly.I haven't had any issues of paint soaking through. Lines nice and clean. Sticks well to both normal emulsion and solvent based paints.
